& [GateRows] is the first defect table
  + [row_001_vorticity_direction_modulus] is coherence defect
    = state_variables: vorticity direction where vorticity is nonzero
    = scale_status: geometric_local_or_critical_contact
    = evolution_relation: conditional_estimate_or_criterion
    = sign_or_coercivity: unknown
    = continuation_contact: vorticity direction coherence regularity criteria
    = propagation_status: assumed
    = first_gap: no autonomous evolution inequality preserving required modulus
  + [row_002_strain_eigenframe_alignment_defect] is strain-geometry defect
    = state_variables: strain tensor eigenframe, vorticity, enstrophy growth terms
    = scale_status: geometric_local
    = evolution_relation: exact identities expose stretching but not monotonicity
    = sign_or_coercivity: indefinite
    = continuation_contact: enstrophy or strain growth control
    = propagation_status: heuristic_to_conditional
    = first_gap: nonlinear strain terms have no one-sided coercive control
  + [row_003_type_i_alignment_defect] is local blowup-profile defect
    = state_variables: scale-invariant local norms and vorticity direction near candidate singularity
    = scale_status: conditional_type_i
    = evolution_relation: conditional estimate in scoped settings
    = sign_or_coercivity: coercive_under_condition
    = continuation_contact: local regularity or singularity-exclusion criteria
    = propagation_status: partial_special_case
    = first_gap: Type I and alignment hypotheses are not derived from arbitrary data
  + [row_004_velocity_direction_defect] is direction-field defect
    = state_variables: velocity direction field and velocity magnitude
    = scale_status: criterion_dependent
    = evolution_relation: conditional criterion
    = sign_or_coercivity: unknown
    = continuation_contact: direction-based regularity criteria
    = propagation_status: assumed
    = first_gap: no flow law forces the direction condition globally

& [GateConclusion] is the defect-functional result
  + [best_partial_candidate] is row_003_type_i_alignment_defect
  + [best_symbolic_fit] is row_001_vorticity_direction_modulus
  + [first_general_lock] is no autonomous evolution inequality preserving or improving the defect for arbitrary smooth data
  + [second_general_lock] is no sign/coercivity strong enough to close a continuation criterion globally
  + [proposition_update] is phase correction should be read as a demand for a dissipative geometric defect inequality, not as a discovered invariant
  + [proof_promotion] is blocked
    = reason: all candidates remain assumed, conditional, indefinite, or special-case

& [NextInquiry] is the next local target
  + [recommended_next] is run a Navier-Stokes reopen saturation reflection unless a concrete defect functional with an evolution inequality is selected
